@node AG-1 "Why?"
When I became aware of my ridicoulus standard workbench, I tested different
Icon-Packages and had to figure out that none of them pleased my taste.
NEWICON is a nice idea but far too colourfull and bright. 
MWB was nice either, but the backpatterns of the icons and the drawers looked
awfull. Anyway, I decided to use MWB because it seemed to be easier to
change the icons.
Most of the MWB Icons were rather nice. Only the backpatterns were anoying.
So what to do best? 
I decided to make brushes from parts of some icons, so that I could paste the
brushes on my favourite patterns. After some time I realized that it was
hard (because stupidous) work. 
So I want to give you the chance to use them without spending weeks for
makeing brushes.
Have fun!

@endnode   


@node AG-2 "What for?"
The brushes have been made to use them on nicer patterns, but they are also
brilliant to make new icons. You can paste them and combine them and make 
good looking icons in minutes.  The devolpement becomes fun.

@endnode   


@node AG-3 "How to use"
I know nothing about your Icon Editor, but most of them should be able to
use the brushes. Here is a `what to do list` for Iconian:
-Use "matte" as brush mode
-load a template-icon
-load a brush
-if you want the brush to be bigger, select scalebrush/dubblex sclaebrush/dubbley
and paste the brush on the template

@endnode   

   
@node AG-4 "Author"
The brushes were mostly cutted out of different icon-packages currently available 
on the aminet. If you find out that some of them were painted by you, don`t be angry,
just feel pleased that I liked the icon :-).

If you want to see more brushes, send me a mail saying that you are using the
package, beacuse I will not send the brushes into the aminet further if I 
get no feedback.
If you have special wishes, send me some Icons or icon-packages, but wait:
If you want to mail larger files, ask me wheter I already have them before
doing so.

